 Nation at a Glance

 Court heat on banquet halls

 New Delhi (PTI): Delhi High Court has ordered the Municipal Corporation of Delhi to close down all banquet halls in the capitals residential areas. 

 Running banquet halls are a perennial source of nuisance for residents, besides causing traffic congestion in the city, and they should go forthwith, a division bench of Justices Vijender Jain and Rekha Sharma said on Friday.

 The court clarified that Thursdays Supreme Court order on dismantling commercial structures in residential areas would apply to banquet halls as well. 

 The directive was given while hearing a PIL complaining about the functioning of commercial farmhouses here.

 The bench said it was not only farmhouses but also scores of banquet halls that have mushroomed in the residential areas illegally, causing severe hardships to the general public. 

 Gucci comes to India

 Mumbai (PTI): Luxury brand Gucci has announced its entry into the Indian market with the Murjani Group and will open its boutiques in Mumbai and Delhi in 2007.

 The Murjani Group is an international entity with a firm understanding of the luxury industry and the Indian market to establish Guccis presence in the country, the company said in a release here.

 Gucci, associated with modern Italian style, distributes its high-quality luxury products through directly operated stores, franchises, duty free boutiques and department stores, it added. 

 Speaker stand

 New Delhi: Speaker Somnath Chatterjee has told the Lok Sabha that he has decided not to accept a court notice challenging Parliaments decision to expel 10 MPs accused in the cash-for-questions scam.

 In my view, the issue was and is non-justiciable. Members cannot be questioned in judicial proceedings, he said on Friday.

 Circus notice

 New Delhi: The Supreme Court has issued notices to the central and state governments on a PIL seeking prohibition of employment of children in circuses. Besides seeking guidelines for recruitment, an NGO has also sought CBI raids to rescue children from circuses.

 Shipbreak panel

 New Delhi (PTI): The Supreme Court has asked the Centre to set up a committee of technical experts, preferably retired naval officers, to assess infrastructure for shipbreaking at Alang in Gujarat.

A 102-year-old Jain devotee went up a hill to witness the mahamastakabhisheka of Bahubali at Shravanbelagola, held once in 12 years. This is the fifth time that he attended the ritual.




